### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/releated to the feature request?

service-worker

### Description

Regarding [VersionReadyEvent](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent#latestVersion)'s currentVersion and latestVersion objects, is it possible to have them contain a new property `updateInfo: string` so that we can use this updateInfo to customize or set the update notification text?  

interface [VersionReadyEvent](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent) {
  [type: 'VERSION_READY'](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent#type)
  [currentVersion: {...}](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent#currentVersion)
  [latestVersion: {...}](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent#latestVersion)
}

https://angular.io/api/service-worker/SwUpdate
```
import {filter, map} from 'rxjs/operators';
// ...
const updatesAvailable = swUpdate.versionUpdates.pipe(
  filter((evt): evt is [VersionReadyEvent](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent) => evt.type === 'VERSION_READY'),
  map(evt => ({
    type: 'UPDATE_AVAILABLE',
    current: evt.currentVersion,
    available: evt.latestVersion,
  })));
  ```

### Proposed solution

Regarding [VersionReadyEvent](https://angular.io/api/service-worker/VersionReadyEvent#latestVersion)'s currentVersion and latestVersion objects, is it possible to have them contain a new property `updateInfo: string` so that we can use this updateInfo to customize or set the update notification text?  

### Alternatives considered

Create an extra endpoint to set the update text

Close #42834

In the new version fo Mocha, all global test functions are from `global`
object instead of `Mocha` object. Adn the current `zone.js` Mocha
patch's logic looks like this.

```
global.describe = Mocha.describe = function() {
  return originalMochaDescribe.apply(this, arguments);
}
```

and `originalMochaDescribe` is the unpathced Mocha implementation
looks like this

```
function describe() {
  return context.describe(...);
}
```

And the `context` will finally delegate to `global.describe()`,
so the current `zone.js` patch causes infinite loop.

This commit will not patch function of `Mocha` object any longer.

